WEBVTT

00:03.420 --> 00:05.547
So damn cold…

00:06.172 --> 00:09.342
How many hours has it been today?

00:09.884 --> 00:13.346
I haven't eaten anything
since this morning, I'm starving…

00:14.681 --> 00:17.434
What should I eat when I get home…?

00:28.278 --> 00:31.447
Yes, but you said bigger is better, right?

00:31.448 --> 00:33.950
If you're gonna make 'em fight,
heavier is better…

00:35.035 --> 00:37.746
Okay, I'll look for one
and call you back. Yes.

00:38.955 --> 00:42.292
What? He's not here. Where did he go?

00:43.001 --> 00:45.503
What a pain… Is he in the bathroom?

00:52.260 --> 00:54.261
Hey, look.

00:54.262 --> 00:55.387
What?

00:55.388 --> 00:57.014
Want to eat a fish sausage?

00:57.015 --> 00:58.307
- Kyapi.
- Hey.

00:58.308 --> 01:00.184
- That guy was in the tournament, right?
- Kyapi.

01:00.185 --> 01:02.936
- He won't eat it!
- Come on, take it! It's fish sausage!

01:02.937 --> 01:04.938
Looks good!

01:04.939 --> 01:07.358
I'm taking the fish sausage!

01:09.736 --> 01:12.738
No cameras on the emergency stairs!

01:12.739 --> 01:14.240
Yo.

01:15.784 --> 01:18.578
Panda, are you sure this is okay?

01:19.120 --> 01:21.622
This could cause trouble later…

01:21.623 --> 01:23.832
It's fine.

01:23.833 --> 01:26.169
Let's lock down the door already.

01:36.763 --> 01:40.600
What? Kirara? Wasn't she with Hakari?

01:42.310 --> 01:43.895
<i>Panda…</i>

01:44.437 --> 01:46.689
<i>And the spiky-haired kid…</i>

01:48.024 --> 01:50.859
<i>So he snuck in with Panda's help…</i>

01:50.860 --> 01:52.486
<i>Is he from Jujutsu High?</i>

01:52.487 --> 01:54.404
<i>Which means Yuji</i>

01:54.405 --> 01:56.783
<i>is from Jujutsu High…</i>

01:57.408 --> 02:00.327
<i>Kinji is in danger!</i>

02:00.328 --> 02:02.831
Boss, I need to talk…

02:06.709 --> 02:08.002
Divine Dogs!

02:09.170 --> 02:10.130
All right.

02:16.511 --> 02:17.971
What? Fushiguro!

02:23.101 --> 02:25.269
<i>My Divine Dog got blown away!</i>

02:25.270 --> 02:28.147
<i>No, based on what Panda said,</i>

02:28.148 --> 02:29.858
<i>it really can't get any closer!</i>

02:30.775 --> 02:31.901
- What?
- What?

02:32.819 --> 02:35.738
<i>'Cause I've already marked Panda.</i>

02:40.076 --> 02:42.035
<i>The monitoring room!</i>

02:42.036 --> 02:44.163
<i>She's going back to Hakari!</i>

02:44.164 --> 02:47.207
Wait, Kirara! We're not your enemies!

02:47.208 --> 02:49.543
We just have something to ask Hakari!

02:49.544 --> 02:52.963
I don't believe you!
I'm disappointed in you, Panda!

02:52.964 --> 02:56.759
What? So this is
the "can't get close" thing for me too.

03:00.430 --> 03:03.141
<i>So Kirara can't get close either?</i>

03:04.934 --> 03:05.851
Fushiguro!

03:05.852 --> 03:08.604
<i>And not just that!</i>

03:08.605 --> 03:12.232
<i>I can't separate from Divine Dog!
What kind of technique is this?</i>

03:12.233 --> 03:13.067
BATTLE ARENA - 2ND FLOOR

03:14.152 --> 03:16.111
- Listen!
- No!

03:16.112 --> 03:17.697
I've cooled off.

04:57.046 --> 04:59.923
<i>This stalemate is perfect!</i>

04:59.924 --> 05:01.425
Kirara!

05:01.426 --> 05:04.511
We're not exactly on Jujutsu High's side.

05:04.512 --> 05:07.598
You know what's happening in Tokyo, right?

05:09.851 --> 05:13.186
Those barriers aren't unrelated.

05:13.187 --> 05:15.731
There was an unprecedented
jujutsu terror attack.

05:15.732 --> 05:18.025
We need Hakari's help!

05:18.026 --> 05:20.777
You're the ones who cut us out first.

05:20.778 --> 05:22.612
Serves you right.

05:22.613 --> 05:24.699
<i>That's why I said we're not on their side…</i>

05:25.366 --> 05:27.326
What happened
between you and the higher-ups?

05:27.327 --> 05:29.328
They clashed with the conservatives.

05:29.329 --> 05:31.371
And being a conservative

05:31.372 --> 05:34.208
isn't just about rules. It's an ideology.

05:34.792 --> 05:38.295
"Jujutsu should be this way."

05:38.296 --> 05:41.506
<i>Kugisaki's technique is a good example.</i>

05:41.507 --> 05:44.385
<i>It's the kind conservatives like.
"Proper jujutsu."</i>

05:45.344 --> 05:47.971
<i>Like those old "cursed video" trends.</i>

05:47.972 --> 05:51.267
<i>As times change,
jujutsu mixes with new tech.</i>

05:52.060 --> 05:56.147
When that reaches techniques,
the conservatives get loud.

05:56.773 --> 05:59.816
Hakari's technique is the textbook case.

05:59.817 --> 06:02.861
Those idiots up top are like that,
so of course they lose.

06:02.862 --> 06:03.904
But you guys

06:03.905 --> 06:07.449
can always have Satoru Gojo
clean up for you, right?

06:07.450 --> 06:10.368
So why would you need us?

06:10.369 --> 06:13.246
So you're lying about "asking for help,"

06:13.247 --> 06:16.626
and you've got another goal.
That's the normal conclusion.

06:17.668 --> 06:19.837
Mr. Gojo was sealed.

06:20.379 --> 06:21.923
That's why we lost.

06:34.268 --> 06:37.730
<i>Right… They don't believe it.</i>

06:38.231 --> 06:40.774
<i>Well, I get it.</i>

06:40.775 --> 06:44.861
<i>But this person is the closest to Hakari.</i>

06:44.862 --> 06:45.780
Rabbit Escape!

06:47.115 --> 06:48.406
Rabbits?

06:48.407 --> 06:50.325
<i>If we persuade her,</i>

06:50.326 --> 06:52.703
<i>negotiating with Hakari will be easier…</i>

06:56.165 --> 06:57.041
<i>Acrux.</i>

06:59.502 --> 07:01.087
<i>Acrux!</i>

07:01.963 --> 07:05.341
<i>That's a lot. What is he trying to do?</i>

07:06.050 --> 07:09.011
<i>My technique marks cursed energy.</i>

07:09.595 --> 07:12.722
<i>So</i> shikigami <i>are treated like the user.</i>

07:12.723 --> 07:16.309
<i>At this rate, you'll get dragged in
like that dog.</i>

07:16.310 --> 07:19.856
<i>Crushed by your own</i> shikigami
<i>and suffocate.</i>

07:30.825 --> 07:33.618
Panda! How was Rabbit Escape?

07:33.619 --> 07:35.745
Cutest thing ever! Second only to me!

07:35.746 --> 07:39.833
I'm asking what you could
and couldn't approach!

07:39.834 --> 07:43.753
Oh, me and the second floor were fine!

07:43.754 --> 07:46.424
Kirara and the monitoring room door
were no good!

07:47.133 --> 07:49.176
Is there a star mark and a name somewhere

07:49.177 --> 07:51.179
on your body?

07:51.804 --> 07:55.891
Huh? Oh. I, M, A, I.

07:55.892 --> 07:57.434
<i>Same here.</i>

07:57.435 --> 08:00.228
- Imai… Imai… Somewhere…
- Found it.

08:00.229 --> 08:02.939
<i>Marked as Acrux,
the same as Rabbit Escape.</i>

08:02.940 --> 08:04.942
<i>Divine Dog might have it too.</i>

08:05.526 --> 08:08.613
<i>I don't know everything yet, but…</i>

08:09.614 --> 08:11.114
I got it.

08:11.115 --> 08:13.576
The trick is constellations.

08:14.076 --> 08:16.411
If you know that much, someone who gets it
really gets it.

08:16.412 --> 08:18.289
The motif constellation is…

08:23.044 --> 08:24.462
The Southern Cross.

08:30.426 --> 08:31.593
Damn it!

08:31.594 --> 08:33.929
<i>We both gave it away!</i>

08:33.930 --> 08:35.847
<i>I had that "No way!" look on my face!</i>

08:35.848 --> 08:36.765
SERIOUSLY?

08:36.766 --> 08:41.269
<i>I didn't have absolute proof
it was the Southern Cross.</i>

08:41.270 --> 08:46.233
<i>But I made a surprised face.
I made them confident.</i>

08:46.234 --> 08:50.238
<i>If they fully see through my technique,
they'll get into the monitoring room.</i>

08:50.738 --> 08:53.198
<i>So I'm stopping them here.</i>

08:53.199 --> 08:54.951
<i>Another stalemate…</i>

08:57.245 --> 08:59.664
<i>But it really was the Southern Cross.</i>

09:00.790 --> 09:02.458
<i>Thanks, Tsumiki.</i>

09:03.209 --> 09:05.293
<i>Still, I don't know any more than that…</i>

09:05.294 --> 09:08.255
<i>Wait. Doesn't the Southern Cross
have four stars?</i>

09:08.256 --> 09:09.590
Fushiguro.

09:10.466 --> 09:12.927
<i>I can still get close to Panda.</i>

09:13.719 --> 09:17.514
Panda,
Southern Cross is four stars, right?

09:17.515 --> 09:19.600
Well… I mean, it's a cross…

09:20.601 --> 09:22.228
Yes. That makes sense.

09:27.316 --> 09:29.276
I thought Kirara assigned each of us

09:29.277 --> 09:31.737
a Southern Cross star

09:32.321 --> 09:35.240
and forced distances.

09:35.241 --> 09:38.118
But Kirara can approach the door.

09:38.119 --> 09:40.704
And you and I can approach each other.

09:40.705 --> 09:42.914
So it's not just simple repulsion

09:42.915 --> 09:46.294
between our stars and Kirara's stars?

09:46.877 --> 09:48.545
If that were the case,

09:48.546 --> 09:51.256
Kirara should've run inside
the monitoring room already.

09:51.257 --> 09:52.924
Oh, right.

09:52.925 --> 09:55.928
If they stuck to the door from the inside,
we would be done.

09:56.512 --> 09:58.806
Then how about this?

09:59.390 --> 10:02.767
Star A can approach Star B,

10:02.768 --> 10:04.853
but B can't approach A.

10:04.854 --> 10:08.315
Each star has compatibility,

10:08.316 --> 10:11.443
and you can only approach compatible ones.
Like rock-paper-scissors.

10:11.444 --> 10:12.402
ROCK-PAPER-SCISSOR THEORY

10:12.403 --> 10:14.529
But you and I can approach

10:14.530 --> 10:17.907
each other freely, right?

10:17.908 --> 10:19.535
So that's not it either.

10:21.787 --> 10:24.581
What if there's a set route,

10:24.582 --> 10:28.168
like a stamp rally,
with an order you must follow?

10:28.169 --> 10:30.170
And identical stars attract.

10:30.171 --> 10:31.296
STAMP RALLY THEORY

10:31.297 --> 10:33.131
I see.

10:33.132 --> 10:36.384
Could the sorcerer be excluded
from their own technique?

10:36.385 --> 10:38.219
That can't be true.

10:38.220 --> 10:40.765
Kirara was forced away
from the <i>shikigami</i> too.

10:41.265 --> 10:45.061
Right now, Kirara is on guard,

10:45.645 --> 10:48.063
worried we'll meet some condition

10:48.064 --> 10:51.149
and slip into the monitoring room
out of sight.

10:51.150 --> 10:54.361
That means there are at least five stars.

10:54.362 --> 10:55.196
Yes.

10:55.863 --> 10:58.573
If the stamp rally theory is true,

10:58.574 --> 11:01.576
and there were only four, either you or I

11:01.577 --> 11:03.370
could approach Kirara.

11:03.371 --> 11:05.664
So there must be a fifth star in between,

11:05.665 --> 11:08.959
and without passing through it,
we can't get close to Kirara or the door.

11:09.585 --> 11:11.920
What if there are six or seven?

11:11.921 --> 11:14.672
I really hope not.

11:14.673 --> 11:17.175
Five stars on a cross
already makes no sense.

11:17.176 --> 11:18.094
<i>If they know…</i>

11:19.428 --> 11:20.346
<i>then of course I'll attack.</i>

11:27.978 --> 11:28.937
What?

11:28.938 --> 11:29.855
Panda!

11:31.941 --> 11:36.277
I'm fine! No problem, Fushiguro!

11:36.278 --> 11:37.696
Find the star!

11:41.992 --> 11:44.160
Hey! Don't throw it!

11:44.161 --> 11:45.037
What?

11:49.041 --> 11:52.168
Just like you,
I put the same Imai star on the car.

11:52.169 --> 11:53.837
If you throw it like with Divine Dog,

11:53.838 --> 11:56.256
it will snap back,
or you'll get yanked in!

11:56.257 --> 11:59.760
<i>To attach a star,
you probably have to touch the target.</i>

12:00.302 --> 12:03.472
<i>But neither I nor Rabbit Escape
touched Kirara.</i>

12:04.014 --> 12:06.015
<i>Only Divine Dog got touched.</i>

12:06.016 --> 12:07.809
<i>Which means</i>

12:07.810 --> 12:09.937
<i>Kirara isn't marking objects,
but cursed energy itself.</i>

12:10.521 --> 12:13.273
<i>To put a star on the door or the car,</i>

12:13.274 --> 12:16.652
<i>someone's cursed energy
had to be infused in advance.</i>

12:21.073 --> 12:22.199
<i>I knew it!</i>

12:23.367 --> 12:26.036
<i>Residuals of cursed energy,
aside from Kirara's, are on the car.</i>

12:26.579 --> 12:28.913
<i>If the technique's range isn't huge,</i>

12:28.914 --> 12:30.833
<i>then the residuals of the other star
should be…</i>

12:42.928 --> 12:45.097
<i>Found it. The fifth star.</i>

12:46.098 --> 12:49.309
<i>There aren't any more traces
besides the three of us.</i>

12:49.310 --> 12:52.353
<i>Kirara had already marked her own
cursed energy with a star.</i>

12:52.354 --> 12:55.565
<i>So to mark an object with my Acrux star,</i>

12:55.566 --> 12:57.859
<i>she can't use her own cursed energy.</i>

12:57.860 --> 13:00.654
<i>That's why she can't fling things at me
as she did with the car.</i>

13:02.490 --> 13:04.575
<i>If I touch that, I can get close to her.</i>

13:07.077 --> 13:09.371
<i>Fushiguro's hypothesis is correct.</i>

13:10.331 --> 13:12.916
<i>Kirara's technique, Love Rendezvous,</i>

13:12.917 --> 13:15.293
<i>uses the Southern Cross as its motif</i>

13:15.294 --> 13:19.006
<i>and assigns five stars
to a target's cursed energy.</i>

13:20.049 --> 13:22.884
<i>To approach another star,</i>

13:22.885 --> 13:25.512
<i>you must follow a fixed sequence.</i>

13:25.513 --> 13:29.058
<i>And matching stars pull toward one side.</i>

13:30.226 --> 13:31.768
You're amazing.

13:31.769 --> 13:34.438
You really get my technique.

13:35.064 --> 13:36.065
Panda!

13:49.036 --> 13:50.162
<i>Huh?</i>

13:50.788 --> 13:54.541
<i>That "sequence" is depth.</i>

13:54.542 --> 13:58.378
<i>Even constellations that look flat
have depth.</i>

13:58.379 --> 14:02.006
<i>Their distance from Earth
is different for each star.</i>

14:02.007 --> 14:03.925
But you assumed I couldn't throw objects

14:03.926 --> 14:07.136
anymore, didn't you?

14:07.137 --> 14:10.765
All I have to do is remove the star
on my cursed energy, Ginan,

14:10.766 --> 14:14.979
and give myself
the same Acrux star as you.

14:20.526 --> 14:22.570
Huh?

14:23.696 --> 14:25.989
<i>Why? From where?</i>

14:25.990 --> 14:27.491
<i>Oh, right! That dog…</i>

14:28.367 --> 14:31.870
<i>You still hadn't released
the shikigami dog yet.</i>

14:31.871 --> 14:35.124
<i>You even figured out which side
gets pulled with matching stars.</i>

14:35.791 --> 14:38.251
<i>Put a wall between me and the</i> shikigami,

14:38.252 --> 14:41.255
<i>and wedge the pulled</i> shikigami
<i>against the wall…</i>

14:41.922 --> 14:45.300
<i>Then, when I step onto the line,
you release the dog!</i>

14:45.301 --> 14:48.345
<i>Damn it! Release Love Rendezvous!</i>

15:07.406 --> 15:09.909
Please listen to us.

15:23.714 --> 15:27.300
Did you really aim that?

15:27.301 --> 15:30.845
You and that dog. You couldn't have known
which one would be pulled.

15:30.846 --> 15:33.515
It was a gamble, but now I get it.

15:34.058 --> 15:36.977
It pulls whoever has
the higher cursed output, right?

15:37.603 --> 15:40.647
At first, I was pulled toward Divine Dog.

15:40.648 --> 15:44.609
But this time, I reinforced myself
to block your attack,

15:44.610 --> 15:45.903
and the result flipped.

15:46.946 --> 15:50.824
You're a first year?
You're seriously kind of adorable…

15:55.746 --> 15:57.163
Please.

15:57.164 --> 16:00.042
We don't have time. Please listen to us.

16:02.378 --> 16:03.754
Fine.

16:11.929 --> 16:15.265
- Itadori!
- Fushiguro. Panda.

16:16.141 --> 16:17.810
Don't interfere.

16:30.197 --> 16:32.074
Don't underestimate me.

16:34.159 --> 16:34.910
- Hey!
- What?

16:37.621 --> 16:40.123
<i>This kid… all this time…</i>

16:40.124 --> 16:42.417
<i>He's not even trying to dodge.</i>

16:42.418 --> 16:43.752
You're nuts.

16:44.795 --> 16:48.006
<i>This isn't like Shibuya.</i>

16:48.007 --> 16:50.967
<i>It's a ritual, basically,</i>

16:50.968 --> 16:52.594
<i>to make Hakari acknowledge me.</i>

16:53.387 --> 16:56.473
<i>I'm not dodging anymore.
I'm not fighting back either!</i>

16:58.392 --> 17:00.768
<i>Until this guy breaks…</i>

17:00.769 --> 17:04.105
Interesting. I'll hear you out.

17:04.106 --> 17:06.357
As long as you're still standing.

17:06.358 --> 17:09.861
Kinji. These kids need your help!

17:09.862 --> 17:11.863
Hear them out.

17:11.864 --> 17:13.824
I said I'm listening!

17:20.289 --> 17:24.417
Hey, Itadori. Why me?

17:24.418 --> 17:26.670
We just met, right?

17:27.171 --> 17:29.214
So why come to me?

17:30.049 --> 17:31.883
Because the upperclassmen

17:31.884 --> 17:33.844
said you were strong.

17:35.471 --> 17:37.514
Thought so.

17:38.015 --> 17:40.349
When a sorcerer
asks another sorcerer for help,

17:40.350 --> 17:43.854
it's basically,
"Put your life on the line with us."

17:45.064 --> 17:50.109
You have to show me the heat
to make me do that!

17:50.110 --> 17:53.696
Right here! Right now!

17:53.697 --> 17:58.242
And you're telling me you came
because someone else said so?

17:58.243 --> 18:02.122
What's Yaga doing?
Weeding out punks like you already!

18:06.168 --> 18:08.587
- I don't have heat.
- What?

18:09.254 --> 18:10.714
I'm a cog.

18:11.715 --> 18:13.592
A cog sorcerer used to

18:14.093 --> 18:15.969
exorcise curses, and kept exorcising them.

18:16.804 --> 18:18.305
I'm a cog.

18:18.889 --> 18:21.891
What? Seriously?

18:21.892 --> 18:24.519
You're boring as hell.

18:24.520 --> 18:25.436
<i>This is bad.</i>

18:25.437 --> 18:26.438
Itadori, that's enough!

18:42.871 --> 18:45.749
It hurts, right?

18:46.583 --> 18:50.129
Mr. Gojo said my cursed energy
feels rougher than other people's.

18:53.173 --> 18:54.591
Did you die?

18:57.010 --> 19:00.054
Hey, Panda and sea urchin-head!

19:00.055 --> 19:02.515
Grab Itadori and get lost!

19:02.516 --> 19:03.851
And don't ever--

19:05.644 --> 19:06.687
What?

19:08.480 --> 19:10.898
No guard, and three hits?

19:10.899 --> 19:13.109
And before that, I wailed on you.

19:13.110 --> 19:15.778
What are you made of?

19:15.779 --> 19:17.864
I'm a cog.

19:17.865 --> 19:19.908
A cog has a role, right?

19:20.993 --> 19:24.120
<i>My role is to keep exorcising curses.</i>

19:24.121 --> 19:27.456
And if that means we need you, Hakari,

19:27.457 --> 19:29.793
I'll stick to you until you say yes.

19:43.932 --> 19:44.933
Hakari.

19:45.601 --> 19:47.811
What's your role?

19:48.770 --> 19:49.897
<i>This brat…</i>

19:51.190 --> 19:53.609
<i>So this is a cog's heat…</i>

19:57.779 --> 19:59.906
Fine. However many hits you want--

19:59.907 --> 20:03.827
Kinji. Aren't you getting worked up?

20:08.040 --> 20:10.334
<i>I can't lie about heat.</i>

20:14.463 --> 20:16.840
- Guys, come down.
- Huh?

20:18.050 --> 20:19.301
It's a deal.

20:21.511 --> 20:23.555
What? So he's…

20:24.056 --> 20:26.390
okay with it?

20:26.391 --> 20:27.308
Yes.

20:27.309 --> 20:28.893
Thank you…

20:28.894 --> 20:30.353
Sure.

20:30.354 --> 20:35.984
I hate those higher-ups,
but Kinji was the most passionate

20:36.568 --> 20:38.362
when he was helping people
at Jujutsu High.

20:38.904 --> 20:39.987
That hurt!

20:39.988 --> 20:41.073
What?

20:42.699 --> 20:46.786
Ring-ring!

20:46.787 --> 20:47.621
- What?
- What?

20:48.205 --> 20:51.123
A rule has been added to the Culling Game

20:51.124 --> 20:53.209
by a player.

20:53.210 --> 20:57.088
Rule nine.
Players may view other players' info.

20:57.089 --> 21:00.383
Their name, points,
number of rules they have added,

21:00.384 --> 21:03.553
and which colony barrier they're in.

21:04.263 --> 21:06.472
A PLAYER CAN ADD A RULE
AFTER GAINING ENOUGH POINTS

21:06.473 --> 21:09.141
THE GAME MASTER MUST ACCEPT NEW RULES,
UNLESS THEY THREATEN THE GAME'S CONTINUITY

21:09.142 --> 21:11.561
Five points have been added.

21:12.104 --> 21:14.398
Of course. I killed them.

21:18.235 --> 21:21.779
Everyone is so damn weak.

21:21.780 --> 21:24.491
People were a bit better 400 years ago.

21:26.952 --> 21:29.413
Where are you, Sukuna?

21:34.042 --> 21:36.544
Your points have exceeded 200.

21:36.545 --> 21:38.254
Do you want to use 100 points

21:38.255 --> 21:41.174
to add a rule to the Culling Game?

21:41.883 --> 21:44.261
Right. Rules…

21:45.137 --> 21:49.474
Names and points,
which measure their strength.

21:50.559 --> 21:53.769
But adding a rule
would reduce one's points.

21:53.770 --> 21:56.231
Then the number of rules
they have added too.

21:56.982 --> 21:59.985
And which colony barrier they're in…

22:00.819 --> 22:03.404
Kogane. Add a rule.

22:03.405 --> 22:06.324
Make all players' information public.

22:06.325 --> 22:09.745
CULLING GAME PLAYER HAJIME KASHIMO

23:42.879 --> 23:44.756
<i>Between dream and reality.</i>

23:45.423 --> 23:48.717
- <i>A curse.
- Why do you know my name?</i>

23:48.718 --> 23:51.637
<i>Once you step inside, you're a player too.</i>

23:51.638 --> 23:54.557
<i>Make them create a way
for Tsumiki to leave the Culling Game.</i>

23:54.558 --> 23:55.976
NEXT EPISODE
